<br>
Also for my sorcerer, I trained in mind magic at lvl 5 (with body and matter magic avalaible to all mages left alone).  Now i have disorientation, telekenisis, domination and mind twisting.  Do ALL these catagories come with mind magic.....or can i specialize in these specific catagories.  Atm, i only have 3 skill branches, i thought there were more?  thanks for the help!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uqlmph.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qlmph</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#E9D756>(12/26/01 6:59:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Magic...</span><hr size=1> Each line of specialization has a different set of spells, for my cleric I also have three lines of spells:<br>
rejuvination-healing &amp; special ressurect spells<br>
enhancements-buffing and a regrowth-type spell line<br>
smite(my personal favorite)-stuns, nuking(holy wrath spec), mesmerization, AEdd, and a pbae shout.<br>
<br>
If you train into one line of spells fully, you are obviously more strong in that line and you will always get the highest lvl spells of that line.<br>
<br>
Now, more onto the casters side.<br>
There are a line of spells that you get at your level, not your skill level, but your experiance level. Then, your other line of spells (refrigeration, etc etc) which, to my findings, are your specialization line of spells. These are the spells which you have gotten through training in Cold, Earth, or Wind.<br>
<br>
I hope this clears it up a little for you. If you are on galahad I would gladly try and help you IG <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>~Qlmph~
*Proud Firestarter of Phoenix Guard* ~40th Cleric~ |Galahad Server| -Retiree of Erollisi Marr/EQ-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/urutroh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rutroh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#E9D756>(1/30/02 4:19:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Magic...</span><hr size=1> A quibbly bug with super low level Theurgists is that until you reach Spec 5 in a line other than Air, you won't get any Spec spells.  So Spec spells from 1st to 4th level in Earth or Ice won't appear until, in some cases, they have already become obsolete.<br>
<br>
As a Theurgist it hardly matters as they are about the only caster that is better off tri-specing to around 30 in all three lines anyway, than just solo-speccing one line to 50, as some Wizards, Runemasters and Eldritches do.<br>
<br>
For me, it's all about Earth.  At 22nd, I'm still killing red Cornish Hunters with 70% of my Power, and I've been killing groups of mobs for the group exp bonuses forever.  At lower levels, the bandit camps are just amazing experience, you target the named leader in the center of the camp, spam every pet at him and just back off.  You get good experience for him, and sometimes up to a 50% bonus for the huge groups of blue, green and grey bandits who try to 'help.'<br>
<br>
By 22nd, I am getting into groups with 36th level people and just chain-casting my bladeturn spells on the main tank during combat.  It saves the Cleric tons of power and allows me to contribute even though the stuff we are facing is red and purple to the mid-30's groupmates...<br>
<br>
But each line has its features.<br>
<br>
A solid ice-Spec and you can Snare, Root, Blast almost as well as a Wizard, although the pet-spamming becomes dangerous (since the pets don't run up and aggro the mobs, they stand close to you and nuke with Ice Blasts...).<br>
<br>
I'm not real clear on the effectiveness of a heavy Air Spec, and with the recent Stun changes, I wouldn't reccomend it right now.<br>
